<subSubSection lastPageId="27" lastPageNumber="826" pageId="26" pageNumber="825" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="26.[160,1156,1669,1728]" box="[160,1156,1703,1728]" pageId="26" pageNumber="825">
<bibRefCitation author="Nieser N" box="[160,296,1703,1728]" pageId="26" pageNumber="825" pagination="157 - 189" refId="ref27806" refString="Nieser N. 1967. The Heteroptera of the Netherlands Antilles - VI Notonectidae. Stud Fauna Curacao Carib Isl. 24 (1): 157 - 189." type="journal article" year="1967">Nieser 1967</bibRefCitation>
). We present the first records of this species from the 
<collectingCountry box="[954,1152,1703,1728]" name="US Virgin Islands" pageId="26" pageNumber="825">US Virgin Islands</collectingCountry>
,
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="27.[160,1155,142,202]" pageId="27" pageNumber="826">collected from brackish pools adjacent to estuaries at Red Hook Salt Pond and in the mangroves at Magens Beach, where it co-occurred with the previous two species.</paragraph>
